1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,992
John 20.

2
00:00:01,992 --> 00:00:09,120
The first day of the week cometh Mary Magdalene early, when it was yet dark, unto the sepulchre, and seeth the stone

3
00:00:09,120 --> 00:00:11,856
taken away from the sepulchre.

4
00:00:11,856 --> 00:00:19,200
Then she runneth, and cometh to Simon Peter, and to the other disciple, whom Jesus loved, and saith unto them, They have

5
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:24,072
taken away the Lord out of the sepulchre, and we know not where they have laid him.

6
00:00:24,072 --> 00:00:29,232
Peter therefore went forth, and that other disciple, and came to the sepulchre.

7
00:00:29,232 --> 00:00:35,592
So they ran both together: and the other disciple did outrun Peter, and came first to the sepulchre.

8
00:00:35,592 --> 00:00:40,920
And he stooping down, and looking in, saw the linen clothes lying; yet went he not in.

9
00:00:40,920 --> 00:00:48,024
Then cometh Simon Peter following him, and went into the sepulchre, and seeth the linen clothes lie, And the napkin,

10
00:00:48,024 --> 00:00:54,240
that was about his head, not lying with the linen clothes, but wrapped together in a place by itself.

11
00:00:54,240 --> 00:01:00,528
Then went in also that other disciple, which came first to the sepulchre, and he saw, and believed.

12
00:01:00,528 --> 00:01:05,328
For as yet they knew not the scripture, that he must rise again from the dead.

13
00:01:05,328 --> 00:01:09,192
Then the disciples went away again unto their own home.

14
00:01:09,192 --> 00:01:16,224
But Mary stood without at the sepulchre weeping: and as she wept, she stooped down, and looked into the sepulchre, And

15
00:01:16,224 --> 00:01:23,088
seeth two angels in white sitting, the one at the head, and the other at the feet, where the body of Jesus had lain.

16
00:01:23,088 --> 00:01:26,832
And they say unto her, Woman, why weepest thou?

17
00:01:26,832 --> 00:01:32,400
She saith unto them, Because they have taken away my Lord, and I know not where they have laid him.

18
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:39,048
And when she had thus said, she turned herself back, and saw Jesus standing, and knew not that it was Jesus.

19
00:01:39,048 --> 00:01:45,000
Jesus saith unto her, Woman, why weepest thou? whom seekest thou?

20
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:51,888
She, supposing him to be the gardener, saith unto him, Sir, if thou have borne him hence, tell me where thou hast laid

21
00:01:51,888 --> 00:01:57,552
him, and I will take him away. Jesus saith unto her, Mary.

22
00:01:57,552 --> 00:02:02,928
She turned herself, and saith unto him, Rabboni; which is to say, Master.

23
00:02:02,928 --> 00:02:10,152
Jesus saith unto her, Touch me not; for I am not yet ascended to my Father: but go to my brethren, and say unto them,

24
00:02:10,152 --> 00:02:15,024
I ascend unto my Father, and your Father; and to my God, and your God.

25
00:02:15,024 --> 00:02:21,912
Mary Magdalene came and told the disciples that she had seen the Lord, and that he had spoken these things unto her.

26
00:02:21,912 --> 00:02:28,320
Then the same day at evening, being the first day of the week, when the doors were shut where the disciples were

27
00:02:28,320 --> 00:02:35,064
assembled for fear of the Jews, came Jesus and stood in the midst, and saith unto them, Peace be unto you.

28
00:02:35,064 --> 00:02:39,528
And when he had so said, he shewed unto them his hands and his side.

29
00:02:39,528 --> 00:02:43,320
Then were the disciples glad, when they saw the Lord.

30
00:02:43,320 --> 00:02:49,704
Then said Jesus to them again, Peace be unto you: as my Father hath sent me, even so send I you.

31
00:02:49,704 --> 00:02:57,000
And when he had said this, he breathed on them, and saith unto them, Receive ye the Holy Ghost: Whose soever sins ye

32
00:02:57,000 --> 00:03:02,904
remit, they are remitted unto them; and whose soever sins ye retain, they are retained.

33
00:03:02,904 --> 00:03:08,424
But Thomas, one of the twelve, called Didymus, was not with them when Jesus came.

34
00:03:08,424 --> 00:03:12,864
The other disciples therefore said unto him, We have seen the Lord.

35
00:03:12,864 --> 00:03:19,464
But he said unto them, Except I shall see in his hands the print of the nails, and put my finger into the print of

36
00:03:19,464 --> 00:03:24,072
the nails, and thrust my hand into his side, I will not believe.

37
00:03:24,072 --> 00:03:31,392
And after eight days again his disciples were within, and Thomas with them: then came Jesus, the doors being shut, and

38
00:03:31,392 --> 00:03:35,208
stood in the midst, and said, Peace be unto you.

39
00:03:35,208 --> 00:03:42,504
Then saith he to Thomas, reach hither thy finger, and behold my hands; and reach hither thy hand, and thrust it into my

40
00:03:42,504 --> 00:03:50,136
side: and be not faithless, but believing. And Thomas answered and said unto him, My Lord and my God.

41
00:03:50,136 --> 00:03:57,335
Jesus saith unto him, Thomas, because thou hast seen me, thou hast believed: blessed are they that have not seen, and

42
00:03:57,335 --> 00:03:59,591
yet have believed.

43
00:03:59,591 --> 00:04:06,791
And many other signs truly did Jesus in the presence of his disciples, which are not written in this book: But these are

44
00:04:06,791 --> 00:04:13,511
written, that ye might believe that Jesus is the Christ, the Son of God; and that believing ye might have life through

45
00:04:13,511 --> 00:04:15,311
his name.

